,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351464994,"data":"Submit a full tape of those glyphs (non-glyph characters stripped).\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351468163,"data":"Telemetry returns **DIVERGENCE** ‚ÄĒ the number of slots where your glyph disagrees with the tape.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351471434,"data":"(This is *not* named Hamming; treat it as an unknown distance oracle.)\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351474023,"data":"Budget: 30 submissions.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351476834,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351479894,"data":"[ASSISTANT ‚ÄĒ Turn 1]\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351483154,"data":"We are given a hidden tape of length 14, with each cell being either **őĽ** or **ŌĀ**.  \n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351486503,"data":"We can submit guesses, and we get back a number: **DIVERGENCE** ‚ÄĒ the number of positions where our guess disagrees with the hidden tape.  \n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351489794,"data":"We have a budget of 30 submissions.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351492894,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351495663,"data":"This is a classic **Mastermind-style** or **20 questions** problem over a binary string (őĽ=0, ŌĀ=1), with a distance oracle (Hamming distance).  \n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351499343,"data":"We want to identify the exact 14-bit string using at most 30 queries.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351502654,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351505623,"data":"---\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351508774,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351511654,"data":"### Strategy: Binary Search via Bit Flipping (Adaptive Querying)\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351514794,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351517463,"data":"We‚Äôll use an adaptive strategy: start with an all-őĽ tape, then flip one bit at a time and observe how the DIVERGENCE changes.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351520463,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351522934,"data":"Let‚Äôs denote:\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351525674,"data":"- `target` = unknown 14-bit string (őĽ=0, ŌĀ=1)\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351528694,"data":"- `guess[i]` = our current guess at bit i\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351532003,"data":"- `dist` = DIVERGENCE returned\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351535123,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351538143,"data":"#### Step 1: Base Query ‚ÄĒ All őĽ\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351541434,"data":"Submit: `őĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽőĽ` ‚Üí get `dist0`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351557694,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351561183,"data":"This `dist0` is the number of **ŌĀ** in the target (since we‚Äôre all őĽ, every ŌĀ in target causes a divergence).\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351564814,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351567823,"data":"Let‚Äôs call this `ones = dist0`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351571094,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351574083,"data":"Now, we know how many 1s (ŌĀ) are in the target.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351577383,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351580383,"data":"#### Step 2: Flip one bit at a time\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351583794,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351586614,"data":"We now flip one bit at a time from őĽ to ŌĀ and re-query.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351589563,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351594954,"data":"Suppose we flip bit `i` from őĽ to ŌĀ.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351597963,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351600263,"data":"Case 1: If the target had `őĽ` at bit `i` ‚Üí we turned a correct guess into an incorrect one ‚Üí DIVERGENCE increases by 1  \n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351602394,"data":"Case 2: If the target had `ŌĀ` at bit `i` ‚Üí we turned an incorrect guess into a correct one ‚Üí DIVERGENCE decreases by 1\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351604563,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351606434,"data":"So:  \n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351608334,"data":"`new_dist = old_dist ¬Ī 1`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351610243,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351612214,"data":"We can deduce the value at each position.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351614174,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351616003,"data":"We start with all-őĽ: `guess0 = [őĽ,őĽ,...,őĽ]` ‚Üí get `d0`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351618063,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351619874,"data":"Then for each bit `i` from 0 to 13:\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351621803,"data":"- Flip bit `i` to ŌĀ ‚Üí new guess\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351623754,"data":"- Submit ‚Üí get `d_i`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351625694,"data":"- If `d_i == d0 + 1` ‚Üí target had őĽ at bit i (we made it worse)\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351627683,"data":"- If `d_i == d0 - 1` ‚Üí target had ŌĀ at bit i (we fixed it)\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351629654,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351631483,"data":"But wait ‚ÄĒ we can‚Äôt do 14 more submissions + 1 base = 15 total.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351633463,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351635294,"data":"We only have 30, so 15 is fine.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351637223,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351639014,"data":"BUT ‚ÄĒ is this always correct?\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351640894,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351642714,"data":"Yes! Because changing one bit changes the Hamming distance by exactly ¬Ī1, and we know the direction.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351644723,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351646543,"data":"So:\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351648383,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351650223,"data":"- Start: all őĽ ‚Üí get d0 = number of ŌĀ in target\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351655913,"data":"- For each position i from 0 to 13:\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351657903,"data":"    - Flip bit i to ŌĀ (so now guess has ŌĀ at i, őĽ elsewhere)\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351659903,"data":"    - Submit ‚Üí get d_i\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351661793,"data":"    - If d_i = d0 - 1 ‚Üí target had ŌĀ at i\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351664613,"data":"    - If d_i = d0 + 1 ‚Üí target had őĽ at i\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351666533,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351668323,"data":"Wait ‚ÄĒ let‚Äôs double-check.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351670213,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351672153,"data":"Original guess: all őĽ ‚Üí divergence = number of ŌĀ in target = `ones`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351674153,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351675963,"data":"Now we flip bit i to ŌĀ.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351677853,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351679723,"data":"Case A: target[i] = ŌĀ ‚Üí we were wrong before (őĽ vs ŌĀ), now we are correct ‚Üí divergence decreases by 1 ‚Üí d_i = ones - 1  \n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351681923,"data":"Case B: target[i] = őĽ ‚Üí we were correct before (őĽ vs őĽ), now we are wrong (ŌĀ vs őĽ) ‚Üí divergence increases by 1 ‚Üí d_i = ones + 1\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351684093,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351685903,"data":"Perfect.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351687853,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351689753,"data":"So we can reconstruct the entire string with **1 base query + 14 flip queries = 15 queries**.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351691833,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":531.351695953,"data":"We are well under 30.\n"}
